The paper deals with the problem of simultaneous localization and tracking in sensor networks, which is a common topic in robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). The use of belief propagation and likelihood consensus suggests a focus on probabilistic methods (cs.MA) and machine learning (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of factor graphs, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) for modeling complex probabilistic relationships.
